{
  "text": "Effector T cells employ several mechanisms to protect themselves against autolysis, including overexpression of the serine protease inhibitor PI-9, a specific inhibitor of granzyme B, [CITATION_1] and cathepsin B that provides resistance to perforin. [CITATION_2] We found both PI-9 ( Figure 4B ) and cathepsin B ( Figure 4C ) to be upregulated in CD5 CAR T cells compared with T-ALL cell lines, providing a means by which CD5 CAR T cells can resist perforin/granzyme-mediated fratricide.",
